28
00:01:48,875 --> 00:01:50,866
[Man]
When Agave sobered up,

29
00:01:50,977 --> 00:01:52,740
she looked down and saw
the head of her son Pentheus

30
00:01:52,812 --> 00:01:55,838
- right there in her hands.
- She thought he was a wild animal.

31
00:01:55,915 --> 00:01:57,712
That's how Dionysus got his revenge.

32
00:01:57,784 --> 00:02:00,116
You a heathen, Henry.

33
00:02:00,186 --> 00:02:01,676
You know what I got right here?

34
00:02:01,754 --> 00:02:04,348
- What?
- Some of that very wine.

35
00:02:04,424 --> 00:02:09,691
"When I was a child, I spake as a child.

36
00:02:11,264 --> 00:02:14,233
"I understood as a child.

37
00:02:14,334 --> 00:02:17,770
"I thought as a child.

38
00:02:17,871 --> 00:02:20,931
"But when I became a man,

39
00:02:21,975 --> 00:02:23,533
I put away all childish things."

